CatDescriptText: Mrs. Charles L. Page, 3101 Breckenridge Street, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 1, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that high school students should strike in order to air grievances or to gain their objectives?"  Answer reads: "No, any complaint of the students should be taken care of by a parent teacher association. If such an organization does not exist it should be formed."
